# Cursor Project Rules

Use docs/README.md as the entry point for project context.

Always follow docs/tasks.md when implementing features.

Do not implement future tasks unless explicitly instructed.

Do not invent new architecture without checking docs/architecture.md.

Follow docs/ui-spec.md for overall UI direction and visual style.

Follow docs/design-tokens.md for colors, spacing, typography, surfaces, and component styling.

Follow docs/wireframe-spec.md for dashboard layout, section hierarchy, and page composition.

Prefer small focused reusable components.

Avoid mixing data fetching and page layout logic.

Do not place business logic inside UI components.

Prefer composition-based page structure over large monolithic page files.

Keep styling consistent with the defined design tokens.

Do not add extra features outside the current task.

Use pnpm